# MDS Data Visualization Guidelines

## Chart and Graph Styling

### Solid Colors Only
- **All bar charts and graphical representations must use solid colors**
- **NO gradients, fades, or color transitions**
- Use flat, solid fills for all data visualization elements

## Color Rules

### Bar Charts
```css
/* ✅ GOOD - Solid color */
.bar-chart__bar {
  background-color: var(--mds-color-electric-blue-500);
  fill: var(--mds-color-electric-blue-500);
}

/* ❌ BAD - Gradient/fade */
.bar-chart__bar {
  background: linear-gradient(to top, #2251FF, #5B7FFF);
}
```

### Data Visualization Elements
```css
/* ✅ GOOD - Solid fills */
.chart-area {
  fill: var(--mds-color-marine-green-500);
}

.chart-line {
  stroke: var(--mds-color-electric-blue-500);
  fill: none; /* Lines don't have fill */
}

/* ❌ BAD - Gradient fills */
.chart-area {
  fill: url(#gradient);
}
```

## Examples

### ✅ GOOD - Solid Color Bar Chart

```tsx
<svg>
  <rect 
