  />
</svg>
```

### ✅ GOOD - Solid Color CSS Chart

```css
.revenue-bar {
  background-color: var(--mds-color-electric-blue-500);
  height: 150px;
}

.expense-bar {
  background-color: var(--mds-color-crimson-red-500);
  height: 80px;
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Gradient Chart

```css
.revenue-bar {
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, #2251FF 0%, #5B7FFF 100%);
}

.pie-slice {
  fill: url(#radialGradient);
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Fade/Opacity Transitions

```css
.area-chart {
  fill: var(--mds-color-electric-blue-500);
  opacity: 0.7; /* Avoid opacity on fills */
}

.bar-chart__bar {
  background: rgba(34, 81, 255, 0.8); /* Use solid color instead */
}
```

## Allowed Visualization Types

All chart types must use solid colors:
- Bar charts (horizontal and vertical)
- Column charts
- Pie charts
- Donut charts
- Area charts (solid fill)
- Line charts (solid stroke)
- Scatter plots (solid points)

## Notes

- Use MDS color tokens for consistency
- Different data series should use different solid colors from the MDS palette
- Hover states may use opacity changes on the entire element, but base colors remain solid
- Borders and outlines should also be solid colors
